Title: Paid Notice: Memorials ZASLAV, H. GARY ESQ. H. GARY ZASLAV, OF WOODLAND PARK, NEW JERSEY, PASSED PEACEFULLY ON FEBRUARY 24, 2018 AT THE AGE OF 87. BORN IN BROOKLYN ON AUGUST 15, 1930, GARY WAS THE SON OF RUSSIAN IMMIGRANTS LOUIS AND BETTY ZASLAV, WHO STARTED WITH NOTHING AND BUILT A THRIVING PLUMBING SUPPLY BUSINESS, LOUIS ZASLAV &amp; SONS, ON PITKIN AVENUE. GARY WENT TO SAMUEL J. TILDEN HIGH SCHOOL IN BROOKLYN, FOLLOWED BY BROOKLYN COLLEGE AND ULTIMATELY BROOKLYN LAW SCHOOL. HE MET THE LOVE OF HIS LIFE, GLORIA DENENBERG, WHILE AT COLLEGE AND THEY WERE MARRIED FOR NEARLY 65 YEARS. HE SERVED HIS COUNTRY AS A RADIO SERGEANT IN THE ARMY IN OCCUPIED GERMANY AFTER WWII. AFTER HIS HONORABLE DISCHARGE, HE BEGAN BUILDING AN INDEPENDENT PRACTICE AS A TRIAL LAWYER WHILE FIRST WORKING AS A LAWYER FOR ASCAP. AS ONE OF THE TWO FOUNDERS OF HIS FIRM, LEWIS, ROBBINS, ZASLAV AND AUERBACH, HE SPECIALIZED IN TORTS, SPECIFICALLY PLAINTIFFS, CIVIL LITIGATION AND MEDICAL MALPRACTICE. HE WAS A MEMBER OF THE MASONS, A PROUD MEMBER OF THE DEMOCRATIC PARTY ESTABLISHMENT OF BROOKLYN, AND A TIRELESS FIGHTER FOR THE CIVIL RIGHTS. GARY ALWAYS FOUGHT TO PROTECT THE RIGHTS OF THOSE WHO COULD NOT FIGHT FOR THEMSELVES, ULTIMATELY CHAIRING THE LAWYERS LODGE OF THE ANTI, DEFAMATION LEAGUE OF B'NAI B'RITH, WHERE HE SERVED PRO BONO TO FIGHT AGAINST DISCRIMINATION IN ALL ITS FORMS, INCLUDING AGAINST THE GROWTH OF HATE GROUPS IN THE U.S. HE RETIRED AT AGE 80. GARY WAS A LOVING HUSBAND, SON, BROTHER, FATHER, UNCLE AND GRANDFATHER. HE IS SURVIVED BY HIS WIFE, GLORIA, HIS THREE SONS, KEN, DAVID AND STEVEN ZASLAV, THEIR WIVES, ERICA, PAM AND JANICE, AND SEVEN WONDERFUL GRANDCHILDREN, JORDAN (AND HIS WIFE, ASHLEY), ALISON, ALEXANDRA, JAMIE, PHOEBE, JAKE AND ABBEY. HE WAS A WONDERFUL FRIEND, MENTOR TO MANY, AND ONE OF THE KINDEST MEN TO WALK THE EARTH. HE WILL BE GREATLY MISSED AND LOVINGLY REMEMBERED. HIS GOOD WORKS LIVE ON THROUGH HIS CHILDREN AND GRANDCHILDREN WHOM HE HAS ALWAYS INSPIRED AND LOVED VERY MUCH. 1

Title: Paid Notice: Memorials ZASLAV, H. GARY ESQ. H. GARY ZASLAV, OF WOODLAND PARK, NEW JERSEY, PASSED PEACEFULLY ON FEBRUARY 24, 2018 AT THE AGE OF 87. BORN IN BROOKLYN ON AUGUST 15, 1930, GARY WAS THE SON OF RUSSIAN IMMIGRANTS LOUIS AND BETTY ZASLAV, WHO STARTED WITH NOTHING AND BUILT A THRIVING PLUMBING SUPPLY BUSINESS, LOUIS ZASLAV &amp; SONS, ON PITKIN AVENUE. GARY WENT TO SAMUEL J. TILDEN HIGH SCHOOL IN BROOKLYN, FOLLOWED BY BROOKLYN COLLEGE AND ULTIMATELY BROOKLYN LAW SCHOOL. HE MET THE LOVE OF HIS LIFE, GLORIA DENENBERG, WHILE AT COLLEGE AND THEY WERE MARRIED FOR NEARLY 65 YEARS. HE SERVED HIS COUNTRY AS A RADIO SERGEANT IN THE ARMY IN OCCUPIED GERMANY AFTER WWII. AFTER HIS HONORABLE DISCHARGE, HE BEGAN BUILDING AN INDEPENDENT PRACTICE AS A TRIAL LAWYER WHILE FIRST WORKING AS A LAWYER FOR ASCAP. AS ONE OF THE TWO FOUNDERS OF HIS FIRM, LEWIS, ROBBINS, ZASLAV AND AUERBACH, HE SPECIALIZED IN TORTS, SPECIFICALLY PLAINTIFFS, CIVIL LITIGATION AND MEDICAL MALPRACTICE. HE WAS A MEMBER OF THE MASONS, A PROUD MEMBER OF THE DEMOCRATIC PARTY ESTABLISHMENT OF BROOKLYN, AND A TIRELESS FIGHTER FOR THE CIVIL RIGHTS. GARY ALWAYS FOUGHT TO PROTECT THE RIGHTS OF THOSE WHO COULD NOT FIGHT FOR THEMSELVES, ULTIMATELY CHAIRING THE LAWYERS LODGE OF THE ANTI, DEFAMATION LEAGUE OF B'NAI B'RITH, WHERE HE SERVED PRO BONO TO FIGHT AGAINST DISCRIMINATION IN ALL ITS FORMS, INCLUDING AGAINST THE GROWTH OF HATE GROUPS IN THE U.S. HE RETIRED AT AGE 80. GARY WAS A LOVING HUSBAND, SON, BROTHER, FATHER, UNCLE AND GRANDFATHER. HE IS SURVIVED BY HIS WIFE, GLORIA, HIS THREE SONS, KEN, DAVID AND STEVEN ZASLAV, THEIR WIVES, ERICA, PAM AND JANICE, AND SEVEN WONDERFUL GRANDCHILDREN, JORDAN (AND HIS WIFE, ASHLEY), ALISON, ALEXANDRA, JAMIE, PHOEBE, JAKE AND ABBEY. HE WAS A WONDERFUL FRIEND, MENTOR TO MANY, AND ONE OF THE KINDEST MEN TO WALK THE EARTH. HE WILL BE GREATLY MISSED AND LOVINGLY REMEMBERED. HIS GOOD WORKS LIVE ON THROUGH HIS CHILDREN AND GRANDCHILDREN WHOM HE HAS ALWAYS INSPIRED AND LOVED VERY MUCH. 1
